    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-16T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-16T13:00:00-05:00" n="402"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d402">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1140 Stimson, H.L./3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Edge</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="48" xml:id="d402fn48">Similar telegrams were sent to the
                        Ambassadors in Germany, Great Britain, and Italy (033.1140 Stimson, H. L./2,
                        4, and 1).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-16T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 16, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>143. For the personal attention of the Ambassador. I have under consideration a
                    visit to Rome, Berlin, Paris, and London. I should like to get a first-hand
                    impression of the situation in each country as it may affect our future
                    problems, including particularly the Disarmament Conference next year and the
                    economic situation. My chief object, however, is rest and recreation, but I do
                    wish to confer with American representatives in each of the aforementioned
                    places. I should like very much to have your frank comment on the advisability
                    of such a trip so far as your post in France is concerned. I would plan to sail
                    for Naples June 13th<note n="48a" xml:id="d402fn48a">The sailing date was
                        subsequently postponed until June 27.</note> and arrive in Paris soon after
                    the first of July. The plan proposed here should be kept entirely
                    confidential.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
